snippet.textDisplay: Harmonic balancer. How many miles on the truck? I would replace the harmonic balancer on the dodge. I have worked on many HD Chevy dump trucks and fords as well. I had one particular dump truck that broke two flex plates in a matter of 1 month. Put in a third one and guess what? It broke as well. The only thing that will affect the flexplate directly is thrust washers (I’m sure you would have wiped out main bearings by now if they were bad) or the harmonic balancer. Replace the balancer. You will thank me later.
